&gt; Frank, I think you&#39;re confusing science and scientists. Science is supposed
&gt; to be a body of knowledge that can explain all known phenomena and predict
&gt; new ones not yet observed. That&#39;s all it is. In a few rare cases, a landmark
&gt; piece of work does just that.
&gt; 
&gt; One example is James Clerk Maxwell&#39;s &quot;A Treatise on Electricity and
&gt; Magnetism.&quot; Not only did it explain all electromagnetic phenomena observable
&gt; (except a couple which were explained by refinements) but it predicted
&gt; things not known at the time Maxwell wrote it. Like Vivaldi antennas.
&gt; 
&gt; Scientists are supposed to look for holes in the existing theories and
&gt; improve on them so they can explain all phenomena. An example is the Bohr
&gt; theory of the atom. It did a great job of predicting the spectral lines of
&gt; hydrogen - the Lyman, Balmer, H series etc. But it didn&#39;t do so well
&gt; explaining the spectral lines of things like uranium. So other theories had
&gt; to come about. And they did. They do a pretty good job of explaining
&gt; existing phenomena and predicting as yet unknown phenomena but they still
&gt; have their flaws.
&gt; However, it is true that some scientists have adopted certain arenas of
&gt; science almost as religions. But note physics deals with PHYSICAL things -
&gt; it says so right in its name. So does chemistry. It&#39;s great if you want
&gt; better batteries, automobile engines or radios. But we&#39;re dealing with
&gt; something here on this group that&#39;s non-physical. To the best I can
&gt; determine, EVP and ITC are produced by spirits. These spirits transcend the
&gt; physical and only use the physical universe for their own purposes.
&gt; 
&gt; Evidently the one thing they love to do is comunicate, whether it be from
&gt; within a human body or outside it or from who knows where. And they are not
&gt; predictable. Science, in dealing with the physical, is not going to explain
&gt; any of this phenomena. Very little is actually known in the realm of
&gt; spirits. Mostly what I see is beliefs. Everyone seems to have their own
&gt; beliefs in this arena; some agree and some conflict. But no one seems to
&gt; have any proof of anything that would take it out of the realm of belief,
&gt; except that the phenomena do exist.
&gt; 
&gt; I wish I knew how the EVP voices can make words that appear at twice or half
&gt; the rate of normal speech, talk backwards, etc. I&#39;d like to learn those
&gt; tricks! And I still don&#39;t know what to think about shadow people. I have
&gt; seen them with my own eyes many, many times. So have others I was with. I
&gt; haven&#39;t been successful at photographing them. For some reason the ones I&#39;ve
&gt; experienced can be seen by human eyes but not photographed. Science lets us
&gt; down on that one. A lot of people think shadow people are evil but I have
&gt; never felt that from them. Again, that&#39;s a belief. No one has proof of it. I
&gt; have felt &quot;evil&quot; from other things. Maybe I&#39;ll tell you about one of these
&gt; &quot;things&quot; that was existing in someone&#39;s attic once. Man, talk about an evil
&gt; presence! But I never got that from shadow people.
&gt; 
&gt; Sorry for going on so long; I just wanted to point out that science and
&gt; scientists are not the same thing and that science has indeed given us some
&gt; things (like Velcro cable ties - the greatest invention of whatever century
&gt; it was invented in).
